if you have any idea (it would help if you know for sure ;) ) what the problem is...then please tell me...with simple instructions on how to fix it. i am no good at this to begin with. so i guess it wasnt too good of an idea to start out with a 525. but what ever.

item.title: Error_game_js5crc [525] giving real rewards for help
item.dc:creator: @MercyScape MercyScape
item.description:
@MercyScape wrote:

I get this on my 525 server, except it gets to ‘Loading World Maps’ or something right at the end, and on my server it starts spamming me with ‘Connection From 127.0.0.1’ and my click later says ‘Error_game_js5crc’ or something like that which is probably the same error, but it’s an error with your source, not your client.

It’s not running properly or it isn’t a 525, but told to try to use a 525 cache.

Someone could have changed the update keys on a 508 like I have tried, and it doesn’t work, 510 update keys on a 508 work fine tho

I just recommend downloading a new source, unless you want to try to find out what’s wrong with it, but don’t download the same one.

Or if you changed something, and compiled correctly and then it stopped working try to undo what you did, this is why I keep a backup after every 5-6 small updates I do and after every big update.

-MercyScape
